# Implementation Plan - Custom Notifications & Error Handling

The user requested "iOS 26 style" notifications instead of native Windows `MessageBox` for launch errors, and better error reporting.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> This plan removes standard `MessageBox` calls in favor of a new `NotificationManager` mechanism.

## Proposed Changes

### UI Components
- **[NEW] `Controls/NotificationToast.xaml`**: A custom UserControl for the toast notification (Title, Message, Icon, Type).
- **[MODIFY] [MainWindow.xaml](file:///c:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/MainWindow.xaml)**: Add a container (e.g., `Grid` or `StackPanel` overlay) for notifications.
- **[MODIFY] [MainWindow.xaml.cs](file:///c:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/MainWindow.xaml.cs)**: Add logic to show/hide notifications.

### Services
- **[NEW] `Services/NotificationService.cs`**: A service to publish notification events.
- **[MODIFY] [MainViewModel.cs](file:///c:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/ViewModels/MainViewModel.cs)**: Subscribe to `NotificationService` and trigger UI updates (or expose `ShowNotification` command).
- **[MODIFY] [LaunchService.cs](file:///c:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/LaunchService.cs)**: Replace `MessageBox.Show` with `NotificationService.ShowError`.

### Cache Cleaning (Optional but requested)
- **[MODIFY] [VersionSettingsDialog.xaml](file:///c:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/VersionSettingsDialog.xaml)**: Add a "Repair / Clean Cache" button to delete version json and indexes, forcing a re-download.

## Verification Plan
1. Trigger a launch error (e.g. disconnect network).
2. Verify a sleek "iOS style" toast appears instead of a MessageBox.
3. Verify the toast auto-dismisses or has a close button.
